1
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:17,040
As the son of a major CEO,
excelling in both academics and sports,

2
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:20,240
Naoya ruled at the very
top of the school's hierarchy.

3
00:00:22,180 --> 00:00:27,180
But I'm the only one
who knows the real Naoya.

4
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:32,540
Constantly bearing the pressure
from his parents and everyone around him,

5
00:00:33,650 --> 00:00:35,080
the expression he shows only to me

6
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:38,180
is so incredibly precious.

7
00:00:39,080 --> 00:00:40,080
Lick it clean.

8
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:44,780
Understood.

9
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:54,660
You really do
whatever you're told, don't you?

10
00:00:57,880 --> 00:00:59,880
If I told you to kiss me,
could you do that too?

11
00:01:28,620 --> 00:01:31,040
To make you even more addicted to this,

12
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:40,840
To make it so you can never leave me,

13
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,600
That's right.

14
00:01:45,440 --> 00:01:49,830
I'm the only one he has.

15
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,000
"The Servant Prince"
(Episode 3)

16
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:08,090
Hey, Takaaki.

17
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,120
Good work today.

18
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:10,739
Are you feeling better?

19
00:03:10,740 --> 00:03:12,250
Yeah, my fever's gone down.

20
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:21,260
Dinner?

21
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:24,510
Yeah, I used the tofu from the fridge.

22
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:29,640
Do you want some too?

23
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:31,580
Sure.

24
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,430
Sorry for the wait.

25
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:41,060
Thanks.

26
00:03:43,430 --> 00:03:46,050
This is the first time
I've had your cooking.

27
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:49,460
Now that you mention it,
I think it really is the first time.

28
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,520
Let's eat.

29
00:04:02,420 --> 00:04:03,520
This is really good.

30
00:04:05,380 --> 00:04:06,470
I'm glad.

31
00:04:20,420 --> 00:04:21,510
It's seriously delicious.

32
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:25,300
Thanks for the meal.

33
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,060
Glad you liked it.

34
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:37,150
What's this all of a sudden?

35
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:38,420
Sorry.

36
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,900
Do you have any idea how much
I've been craving you until yesterday?

37
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,300
Yeah.

38
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:46,120
You looked so cute wanting me,
so I pretended not to notice.

39
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,240
Huh?

40
00:04:48,340 --> 00:04:50,860
You really have a twisted personality.

41
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:03,320
Just let me hold you like this.

42
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,280
Hey, Takaaki.

43
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,410
I...

44
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:28,980
I'm planning to get a part-time job.

45
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,080
Huh?

46
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:40,920
I looked around online today.

47
00:05:41,486 --> 00:05:43,366
You see, that Grisa Building.

48
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,680
A restaurant inside is hiring right now.

49
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:49,530
I sent in my resume
and they got back to me right away.

50
00:05:49,890 --> 00:05:54,010
It's close by,
and it seems they're really short-staffed.

51
00:05:56,780 --> 00:05:57,780
I see.

52
00:05:58,533 --> 00:06:00,434
I know I should probably
find a full-time job,

53
00:06:00,465 --> 00:06:02,493
but I'll treat this as practice for
getting back into the real world.

54
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:07,200
Got it.

55
00:06:10,990 --> 00:06:12,090
I'll go wash the dishes.

56
00:06:16,830 --> 00:06:19,330
You taking on longer shifts is a huge help.

57
00:06:20,063 --> 00:06:22,223
So, we're counting on you.

58
00:06:22,790 --> 00:06:23,790
Great.

59
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,920
Here you go.

60
00:06:26,090 --> 00:06:27,550
This is your uniform, Goto-kun.

61
00:06:28,130 --> 00:06:29,386
I'm expecting great things from you.

62
00:06:29,410 --> 00:06:30,410
Understood.

63
00:06:36,670 --> 00:06:39,150
Sorry to keep you waiting, party of two.

64
00:06:39,330 --> 00:06:40,330
Right this way.

65
00:06:40,490 --> 00:06:42,769
Welcome. Please have a
seat and wait a moment.

66
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:46,690
Maybe it's because the upper floors
have offices and a hotel,

67
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:49,690
the customer base is pretty diverse.

68
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:53,780
That guy is the most
efficient one here, right?

69
00:06:56,620 --> 00:06:57,890
His customer service,

70
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:00,710
his movement,

71
00:07:02,450 --> 00:07:03,970
and the way he supports his coworkers...

72
00:07:05,070 --> 00:07:06,150
I see.

73
00:07:09,380 --> 00:07:11,450
- Excuse me.
- Please wait just a moment.

74
00:07:13,450 --> 00:07:16,970
It looks like they really
are severely understaffed.

75
00:07:23,170 --> 00:07:25,170
I'm Goto Naoya, starting work here today.

76
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:26,630
Nice to meet you all.

77
00:07:29,030 --> 00:07:30,030
Nice to meet you.

78
00:07:30,210 --> 00:07:31,700
I'm Mori, the floor manager.

79
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:33,870
Ah, from yesterday...

80
00:07:34,890 --> 00:07:36,510
I'm Harumoto Nana, a part-timer.

81
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:39,000
I'm Suzuki Hiroki, a part-timer.

82
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:44,020
Since it's your first day, you'll be training
while helping out with the lunch rush.

83
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:46,170
Harumoto, make sure to show him the ropes.

84
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:47,450
Got it.

85
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:50,020
We've been packed lately,
so it's great to have you here.

86
00:07:50,090 --> 00:07:51,370
We really appreciate it.

87
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,300
We couldn't handle it all on our own.

88
00:07:53,930 --> 00:07:56,360
We're counting on you, Goto-kun.

89
00:07:57,550 --> 00:07:58,550
Understood.

90
00:08:00,830 --> 00:08:02,470
Sorry for the wait.

91
00:08:02,490 --> 00:08:03,730
Here is the spicy tomato pasta.

92
00:08:05,810 --> 00:08:07,030
And the side salad.

93
00:08:08,390 --> 00:08:09,480
Enjoy your meal.

94
00:08:12,230 --> 00:08:14,850
- Welcome. Party of two?
- Yes, two.

95
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,030
Right this way.

96
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:21,330
- Excuse me.
- Yes, how can I help you?

97
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:24,820
What kind of ingredient is the Ise lobster?

98
00:08:24,937 --> 00:08:26,646
The Ise lobster is a delicacy...

99
00:08:26,670 --> 00:08:28,769
Wow, Goto-kun.

100
00:08:28,770 --> 00:08:30,290
He hit the ground running.

101
00:08:30,690 --> 00:08:31,740
Ouch...

102
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:34,550
Enjoy your meal.

103
00:08:36,230 --> 00:08:38,050
Hey, you there.

104
00:08:39,050 --> 00:08:40,060
Yeah, you.

105
00:08:40,930 --> 00:08:41,930
Yes?

106
00:08:42,710 --> 00:08:44,670
Move me to that table over there.

107
00:08:48,610 --> 00:08:49,650
I'm very sorry, sir.

108
00:08:50,070 --> 00:08:51,669
That table is already reserved.

109
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:52,870
Don't give me that.

110
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:57,010
It's been empty
since before I even got here.

111
00:09:00,090 --> 00:09:02,550
We sincerely apologize
for making you feel uncomfortable.

112
00:09:03,870 --> 00:09:07,060
You are more than welcome to make
a reservation before your next visit.

113
00:09:07,210 --> 00:09:08,940
That's enough, stop it.

114
00:09:13,770 --> 00:09:15,090
Excuse me.

115
00:09:20,010 --> 00:09:21,010
Good work today.

116
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:23,350
Good work.

117
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:26,470
Goto-kun,
we really owe you for earlier.

118
00:09:27,060 --> 00:09:28,769
You handled that complaint perfectly.

119
00:09:28,770 --> 00:09:30,029
Seriously.

120
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:31,569
I had no idea what to do.

121
00:09:31,570 --> 00:09:32,769
But you handled it so calmly.

122
00:09:32,770 --> 00:09:34,020
That was amazing.

123
00:09:34,110 --> 00:09:35,709
We definitely learned a lot from that.

124
00:09:35,710 --> 00:09:36,730
Thank you.

125
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:38,780
It was nothing.

126
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:40,960
We're counting on you again tomorrow.

127
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,350
Understood.

128
00:09:52,130 --> 00:09:55,590
I feel like I'm fitting in
better than I expected.

129
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:04,420
I've always lived my life
as the CEO's son.

130
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:07,810
Naoya-san, as expected
of the president's son.

131
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:09,330
You're truly outstanding.

132
00:10:09,370 --> 00:10:11,370
Everyone has such high hopes for you.

133
00:10:11,410 --> 00:10:13,550
Please let us follow you
for the rest of our lives.

134
00:10:13,570 --> 00:10:15,359
Let's build a truly great company together.

135
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,700
Those sycophants,

136
00:10:18,070 --> 00:10:19,070
in the blink of an eye,

137
00:10:19,530 --> 00:10:20,779
turned their backs on me.

138
00:10:20,803 --> 00:10:22,862
Ruining the company.
What a useless piece of trash.

139
00:10:23,210 --> 00:10:25,926
As expected, relying solely on his parents'
coattails, he can't do anything right.

140
00:10:25,950 --> 00:10:29,960
No one has ever truly
looked at me for who I am.

141
00:10:32,460 --> 00:10:35,090
But working just as an ordinary
'Goto Naoya',

142
00:10:35,110 --> 00:10:36,150
Thank you for coming.

143
00:10:36,190 --> 00:10:37,300
We hope to see you again.

144
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:42,360
It is surprisingly fun.

145
00:10:49,850 --> 00:10:51,170
Looks like things are going well.

146
00:10:52,210 --> 00:10:53,410
It's going alright.

147
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:02,360
If you have some spare time,

148
00:11:02,910 --> 00:11:04,680
could you help me out a bit?

149
00:11:06,110 --> 00:11:07,110
Huh?

150
00:11:07,590 --> 00:11:09,090
I've been so busy lately.

151
00:11:10,070 --> 00:11:13,930
It'd be great if you could pre-check
the documents submitted to me.

152
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,030
Is it okay for me to look at them?

153
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,670
Yes.

154
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:20,840
Hmm.

155
00:11:35,270 --> 00:11:36,270
Ah.

156
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:38,230
There's a typo here.

157
00:11:38,930 --> 00:11:39,930
Huh?

158
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:42,910
You're right.

159
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:46,820
By the way, this form,

160
00:11:47,590 --> 00:11:50,040
wouldn't it be better
to revise it like this?

161
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:51,580
True.

162
00:11:59,503 --> 00:12:00,623
Become a full-time employee?

163
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:02,790
Mori-san is planning to leave.

164
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:06,140
I was thinking it'd be great if we
could leave the floor to you, Goto-kun.

165
00:12:06,390 --> 00:12:08,450
If it's you, Goto-kun, I can leave it
in your hands with peace of mind.

166
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:10,680
I'd be thrilled if you'd
seriously consider it.

167
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:14,970
Okay, thank you.

168
00:12:15,050 --> 00:12:16,050
I'll think about it.

169
00:12:17,230 --> 00:12:19,810
This seasonal fruit cake
is also highly recommended.

170
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:21,390
Thank you.

171
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:22,910
Excuse me.

172
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:27,940
A full-time employee, huh.

173
00:12:28,610 --> 00:12:30,400
I never even considered it before.

174
00:12:32,530 --> 00:12:35,020
Excuse me, I'm here to meet someone.

175
00:12:36,810 --> 00:12:37,810
Understood.

176
00:12:40,010 --> 00:12:42,250
You're the guest who reserved
the private room, correct?

177
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:54,170
You...

178
00:12:54,650 --> 00:12:56,510
Right, I need to show him to his seat...

179
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:58,310
If it isn't Naoya.

180
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:03,590
Look at you dressed like that.

181
00:13:08,580 --> 00:13:10,900
I wondered where you'd scurried off to.

182
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:13,350
To think you were in a place like this,

183
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,780
doing menial work even a monkey could do.

184
00:13:18,830 --> 00:13:23,500
But I guess this just proves
this is all you were ever capable of.

185
00:13:27,270 --> 00:13:28,470
Sir,

186
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:29,850
I am very sorry.

187
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,550
I will show you to your seat.

188
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:34,109
Mori-san, I'm fine.

189
00:13:34,110 --> 00:13:35,980
No, you look terrible.

190
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:37,549
Go take a break in the back.

191
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:38,630
Please, hurry up.

192
00:13:39,270 --> 00:13:41,330
Understood. Right this way.

193
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,440
I apologize for not recognizing
that was your son earlier.

194
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:02,460
No.

195
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,760
I don't consider him my son.

196
00:14:05,836 --> 00:14:09,326
At his age, it turns out that he's
only capable of such lowly work.

197
00:14:10,470 --> 00:14:12,700
His mother, who died early,

198
00:14:13,350 --> 00:14:15,330
was also a vulgar woman.

199
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:18,200
Blood doesn't lie.

200
00:14:18,910 --> 00:14:20,040
How can you say that...

201
00:14:21,190 --> 00:14:22,560
That's all in the past.

202
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:25,710
I guess I was just young
and reckless back then.

203
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,980
She was nothing but a
pretty face and a nice body.

204
00:14:31,070 --> 00:14:34,090
I hear you have a son
with a very bright future.

205
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:39,030
That's the son I have with my current wife.

206
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:42,790
Yuma joined our company this year.

207
00:14:42,990 --> 00:14:44,980
That's certainly something
to look forward to.

208
00:14:51,510 --> 00:14:54,590
He looks to be about my age.

209
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:58,320
Do you have any regrets in life?

210
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,560
Excuse me.

211
00:15:02,650 --> 00:15:03,650
President Goto.

212
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:05,689
About the redevelopment project...

213
00:15:05,690 --> 00:15:06,740
Oh.

214
00:15:15,470 --> 00:15:16,470
Goto-kun.

215
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,140
Are you holding up okay?

216
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,000
Mori-san.

217
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:24,980
It's been a while since
we've had such a difficult customer.

218
00:15:26,330 --> 00:15:27,980
I'm so sorry about my father.

219
00:15:28,050 --> 00:15:30,090
Oh, he really took me by surprise.

220
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:32,360
He completely treated me like a commoner.

221
00:15:33,630 --> 00:15:34,990
A commoner...

222
00:15:37,110 --> 00:15:40,540
I heard your mother passed
away when you were young?

223
00:15:41,650 --> 00:15:43,480
He even told you that?

224
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:45,590
Yeah.

225
00:15:48,070 --> 00:15:51,770
My mother was exactly what
my father would call a 'commoner.'

226
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:56,680
What a stubborn piece of work.

227
00:15:57,370 --> 00:15:58,550
Get out of my sight.

228
00:15:59,770 --> 00:16:01,080
Get out.

229
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:14,680
It's fine.

230
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:17,210
And because of that,

231
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:21,080
I wanted my father to acknowledge
my abilities no matter what.

232
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:26,160
Even though it was just a pipe dream.

233
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,600
I'm still single at my age.

234
00:16:31,930 --> 00:16:33,570
Not that I regret it,

235
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:37,050
But if I had a son like you,

236
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:39,860
you would absolutely be my greatest pride.

237
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:49,100
Thank you for bailing me out today.

238
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:54,530
Goto-kun.

239
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:57,150
I'll see you tomorrow, right?

240
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,430
I'm on the schedule.

241
00:17:18,990 --> 00:17:21,510
The last time I had a meal with my father

242
00:17:21,660 --> 00:17:24,060
was at an unexpected matchmaking dinner.

243
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:28,110
Thank you all so much for taking the time
out of your busy schedules to be here today.

244
00:17:29,610 --> 00:17:31,810
It's a pleasure to meet you.

245
00:17:32,770 --> 00:17:33,770
The pleasure is mine.

246
00:17:34,456 --> 00:17:38,016
I hear Mika-san and Naoya
graduated from the same university?

247
00:17:38,180 --> 00:17:39,050
Yes, we did.

248
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:40,340
Even from the same department.

249
00:17:41,090 --> 00:17:42,090
Is that so?

250
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:44,490
Then you two must have a lot to talk about.

251
00:17:51,850 --> 00:17:53,649
Well then, we'll leave you two to it.

252
00:17:53,650 --> 00:17:55,320
Yes, let's go.

253
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,690
Naoya, you know what to do.

254
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:19,740
These kinds of situations
always make me so nervous.

255
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:21,640
Yeah, they do.

256
00:18:22,010 --> 00:18:25,730
I was in the international
relations club in college.

257
00:18:25,930 --> 00:18:26,970
What about you, Naoya-san?

258
00:18:27,310 --> 00:18:29,910
Oh, I wasn't really in any clubs.

259
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:32,110
That makes sense.

260
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:35,820
After all, you had already decided
to take over your father's business.

261
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:38,960
I could feel my body slowly turning cold.

262
00:18:40,450 --> 00:18:42,490
No matter how hard I tried,

263
00:18:44,120 --> 00:18:46,990
If anyone found out I was moaning
in the arms of another man...

264
00:18:48,620 --> 00:18:53,200
I would be nothing but
a disgrace to my father.

265
00:19:03,830 --> 00:19:04,830
President.

266
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:07,450
We still haven't heard back
from Goto Construction.

267
00:19:08,190 --> 00:19:09,050
Is that so?

268
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:11,060
If they cancel the contract...

269
00:19:12,060 --> 00:19:13,270
That's to be expected.

270
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:15,760
If anything, they're the ones
who are going to be in trouble.

271
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:33,040
He's not back yet?

272
00:19:42,050 --> 00:19:43,770
The lights aren't even on. What's going on?

273
00:19:47,570 --> 00:19:49,240
I didn't realize it was already dark.

274
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:57,930
Did something happen?

275
00:19:59,343 --> 00:20:02,143
I messed up at work.

276
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:04,790
Messed up?

277
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,110
Hey, hold me.

278
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:12,950
You can do whatever you want to me.

279
00:20:40,290 --> 00:20:41,290
I got it.

280
00:21:00,590 --> 00:21:01,220
What are you doing?

281
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:02,220
Hold still.

282
00:21:02,590 --> 00:21:03,990
It's hard to massage you like this.

283
00:21:04,180 --> 00:21:05,940
Didn't you say I could
do whatever I wanted?

284
00:21:09,610 --> 00:21:10,710
I don't care about that.

285
00:21:10,990 --> 00:21:12,090
Just hold me already.

286
00:21:13,550 --> 00:21:15,580
You can be as rough
as last time, I don't mind.

287
00:21:20,670 --> 00:21:21,730
Takaaki.

288
00:21:24,820 --> 00:21:25,530
Look...

289
00:21:25,610 --> 00:21:27,470
This isn't like last time.

290
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:34,600
Didn't you say you were done
using me to punish yourself?

291
00:21:38,170 --> 00:21:42,460
It's times like this
when you tempt me so easily.

292
00:21:51,990 --> 00:21:53,180
That's not what I meant...

293
00:21:59,770 --> 00:22:00,790
I'm sorry.

294
00:22:10,070 --> 00:22:11,180
What happened today?

295
00:22:17,210 --> 00:22:20,270
I ran into my father
at my part-time job.

296
00:22:25,490 --> 00:22:26,680
I see.

297
00:22:30,030 --> 00:22:31,030
Naoya.

298
00:22:32,970 --> 00:22:33,970
Do you have any idea?

299
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,830
Being here with you right now,

300
00:22:39,490 --> 00:22:42,030
just how incredibly happy I am?

301
00:22:44,730 --> 00:22:45,730
Yeah.

302
00:22:47,650 --> 00:22:50,880
Because I still have you by my side.

303
00:22:55,510 --> 00:22:56,750
Ah, Takaaki.

304
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:58,220
That feels so good.

305
00:23:05,590 --> 00:23:06,590
I love you.

306
00:23:07,270 --> 00:23:08,270
Naoya.

307
00:23:09,550 --> 00:23:12,860
Instead of always focusing
on what you don't have,

308
00:23:13,870 --> 00:23:16,620
you should cherish what you do have.

309
00:23:17,310 --> 00:23:18,310
Takaaki.

310
00:23:20,890 --> 00:23:21,890
I love you.

311
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:30,800
(Next Episode)

312
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:33,000
It's been a while, brother.

313
00:24:33,023 --> 00:24:34,077
If I can't control the things I want,

314
00:24:34,101 --> 00:24:34,667
[Naoya Goto's banking passbook]

315
00:24:34,720 --> 00:24:36,969
and keep them tied to
me, I get incredibly anxious.

316
00:24:36,970 --> 00:24:38,459
Can I come over to your place today?

317
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,589
I'm sorry.
Cancel the rest of my schedule.

318
00:24:40,590 --> 00:24:44,820
The thought of having to let you go
is what hurts the most.

